<h1>Problem 1999 - 2023 ELMO, P1 of 6, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(m\) be a positive integer. Find, in terms of \(m\), all polynomials \(P(x)\) with integer coefficients such that for every integer \(n\), there exists an integer \(k\) such that \(P(k)=n^m\).</p>
